Interface LongArrayFS

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable, CommonArrayFS<Long>, FeatureStructure
All Known Subinterfaces:
LongArrayFSImpl
All Known Implementing Classes:
LongArray
public interface LongArrayFS extends CommonArrayFS<Long>
Long array interface. To create a long array object, use CAS.createLongArrayFS(int) or new LongArray(aJCas, length)

    • copyToArray

      void copyToArray(int srcOffset, long[] dest, int destOffset, int length) throws ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
      Copy the contents of the array from start to end to the destination destArray with destination offset destOffset.
      Parameters:
      srcOffset - The index of the first element to copy.
      dest - The array to copy to.
      destOffset - Where to start copying into dest.
      length - The number of elements to copy.
      Throws:
      ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - If srcOffset < 0 or length > size() or destOffset + length > destArray.length.
